Japan's Nomura Securities Co. Ltd. announced  Wednesday pre-tax earnings of 50.7 billion yen (492 million dollars) for the  year to March, up sharply from 2.38 billion yen a year earlier.
The country's biggest securities company said operating revenue climbed 16  percent to 399 billion yen in the same period.
Nomura forecast a further increase in earnings to 90 billion yen in the  current year with revenue climbing to 430 billion yen.
